////////////////ALPT_2635 requirment/////////////////
Conduct Advanced Person Search Using Fuzzy/Soundex Capability via Multi-Field Search Screen <Enabler>

Key details:
	Story:
As an Administration Product Team Developer on the Advanced Person Search screen, I will be able to conduct a Person Search using fuzzy and phonetic (Soundex) matching logic through a multi-field search screen, so that I can find Person Records even when exact spelling, formatting, or pronunciation of identifiers is not known, while supporting development of search algorithm logic before it is applied to the single-line search bar.
Acceptance Criteria

Acceptance Criteria 1 – Display Search Fields and Default Matching Behavior
Given I am on the Advanced Person Search screen,
When the screen loads,
Then the system must display the following search fields:

First Name

Last Name

Date of Birth

Person ID

Address
	Address Line 1 
	Address Line 2
	city
	state
	Zip code
	county

Phone Number

SSN

Gender

Race

And provide an “Exact Matches Only” toggle or checkbox,
And when the toggle is not selected, the system must default to fuzzy and phonetic (Soundex) matching logic.

Acceptance Criteria 2 – Fuzzy Search Using Single Identifier
Given I am on the Advanced Person Search screen with Exact Matches Only not selected,
When I enter a value in any one of the available fields with minor variations like spelling differences, typos, or formatting differences,
And I click Search,
Then the system must return Person Records that closely match the entered value,
Even if there are minor differences in spelling, character sequence, or formatting.

Acceptance Criteria 3 – Fuzzy Search Using Multiple Identifiers
Given I am on the Advanced Person Search screen with Exact Matches Only not selected,
When I enter values across two or more fields,
And I click Search,
Then the system must return Person Records that closely match the combination of entered identifiers,
Even if there are minor variations such as spelling errors or typingl differences.

Acceptance Criteria 4 – Phonetic Matching (Soundex Support)
Given I am on the Advanced Person Search screen,
When I enter a value in any of the fields,
And I click Search,
Then the system must return Person Records where the stored values sound similar to the entered value,
Even if the spelling differs.

Acceptance Criteria 5 – Align Fuzzy Matching with Future Single-Line Search
Given the multi-field search screen is being used as an interim solution,
When fuzzy and phonetic matching logic is applied,
Then the system must ensure that this behavior aligns with the future single-line search bar,
So that the search algorithm can be transitioned without rework.

Business Rules:

Fuzzy matching must allow for minor spelling differences, typographical errors, and formatting variations.

When Exact Matches Only is not selected, fuzzy and phonetic logic must be applied by default.

Matching must support both single-field and multi-field searches.
